1. arithematic operations on a file executed by 'bc' command.
2. merging files using 'cat' command.
3. finding differences in files using 'cmp' command.
4. finding differences in files using 'diff' command.
5. finding commonality in giles using 'comm' command.

6. using 'chmod' to change file permissions.
r - 4
w - 2
x - 1

chmod ugo filename
u - user - [0, 7]
g - user_group - [0, 7]
o - others - [0, 7]

chmod u+w filename
chmod g-x filename

7. head -k filename
displays first k lines

8. tail -k filename
displays last k lines

9. vi basics
:x write and save
:n goes to line n
:u undo the changes

10. shell scripting basics
vi filename.sh
#!/bin/sh
#to write comment
commands
give execute permission
execute using ./filename.sh

set variable as usual.
to print value, use echo $name.


